text.section:
If the property is redeemed, the person redeeming shall pay the collector:
the total lien amount paid at the tax sale for the property together with interest;
any taxes, interest, and penalties paid by any holder of the certificate of sale;
any taxes, interest, and penalties accruing after the date of the tax sale;
in the manner and by the terms required by the collector, any expenses or fees for which the plaintiff or the holder of a certificate of sale is entitled to reimbursement under § 14-843 of this subtitle; and
for vacant and abandoned property sold under § 14-817 of this subtitle for a sum less than the amount due, the difference between the price paid and the unpaid taxes, interest, penalties, and expenses.
